Text.SourceString: Hmm. Yeah?//<portrait=happy>Ah, the new resident.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. Yeah?//<portrait=happy>Ah, the new resident.

Text.SourceString: My ex told me about the grandchild of some farmer moving back in. That must be you.//See you around!
Text.LocalizedString: My ex told me about the grandchild of some farmer moving back in. That must be you.//See you around!

Text.SourceString: I personally never saw the appeal of living here in Starlet Town.//It’s a bit too sleepy for my taste.
Text.LocalizedString: I personally never saw the appeal of living here in Starlet Town.//It’s a bit too sleepy for my taste.

Text.SourceString: I make a decent amount of money from my store.//<portrait=annoyed>Well, I used to, anyway. When there were a lot of tourists before the oil spill incident.
Text.LocalizedString: I make a decent amount of money from my store.//<portrait=annoyed>Well, I used to, anyway. When there were a lot of tourists before the oil spill incident.

Text.SourceString: My girls love jackfruit pies, so I always make sure to bring some every time I visit.
Text.LocalizedString: My girls love jackfruit pies, so I always make sure to bring some every time I visit.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Suki</> is a super mom. Whoever ends up with her will be one lucky –//Ah, my jealousy is showing.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Suki</> is a super mom. Whoever ends up with her will be one lucky –//Ah, my jealousy is showing.

Text.SourceString: Spring is when retailers like myself get the new clothing catalogs.//Spring and Fall, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is when retailers like myself get the new clothing catalogs.//Spring and Fall, actually.

Text.SourceString: It’s very bright out lately.//<portrait=normal>It’s the Spring sun. It’s waking up again.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s very bright out lately.//<portrait=normal>It’s the Spring sun. It’s waking up again.

Text.SourceString: My daughter is a very good artist.//I want to send her to Summer art programs when she’s a bit older.
Text.LocalizedString: My daughter is a very good artist.//I want to send her to Summer art programs when she’s a bit older.

Text.SourceString: The inn, where I stay when I’m here, is beautiful this time of year.//It’s right on the water, you see.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll stay a little longer this Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn, where I stay when I’m here, is beautiful this time of year.//It’s right on the water, you see.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll stay a little longer this Summer.

Text.SourceString: Ah, Starlet Town in Fall.//What a place to be.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, Starlet Town in Fall.//What a place to be.

Text.SourceString: My visits here are never <Italic>not</> special in Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: My visits here are never <Italic>not</> special in Fall.

Text.SourceString: It’s the twins’ birthday season.//I got them pies and cases of green smoothies last year. That was a hit.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the twins’ birthday season.//I got them pies and cases of green smoothies last year. That was a hit.

Text.SourceString: My baby likes to play in the snow.//She’s creative and likes to make things with her hands as well. I’m very proud.
Text.LocalizedString: My baby likes to play in the snow.//She’s creative and likes to make things with her hands as well. I’m very proud.

Text.SourceString: Ah, rain… The productivity killer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, rain… The productivity killer.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the storm… A productivity killer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the storm… A productivity killer.

Text.SourceString: Ah, rain… The productivity killer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, rain… The productivity killer.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the storm… A productivity killer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the storm… A productivity killer.

Text.SourceString: This suit isn’t made for the rain, I’m afraid. Please excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: This suit isn’t made for the rain, I’m afraid. Please excuse me.

Text.SourceString: This suit isn’t made for the rain, I’m afraid. Please excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: This suit isn’t made for the rain, I’m afraid. Please excuse me.

Text.SourceString: The rain is kind of cold.//Excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: The rain is kind of cold.//Excuse me.

Text.SourceString: It’s kind of cold in this storm.//Excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s kind of cold in this storm.//Excuse me.

Text.SourceString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.
Text.LocalizedString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.

Text.SourceString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.
Text.LocalizedString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.

Text.SourceString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.
Text.LocalizedString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.

Text.SourceString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.
Text.LocalizedString: Not the best idea to stand around in this rain.//We should go inside somewhere if you want to chat.

Text.SourceString: My little empanada’s very good at art. Maybe someday she’ll be in the fashion industry, following in my footsteps.
Text.LocalizedString: My little empanada’s very good at art. Maybe someday she’ll be in the fashion industry, following in my footsteps.

Text.SourceString: I want to spend more of my time here, but ah, you know – business.//It won’t run itself. The store back home is much larger and needs more attention.
Text.LocalizedString: I want to spend more of my time here, but ah, you know – business.//It won’t run itself. The store back home is much larger and needs more attention.

Text.SourceString: My <NpcName>Valentina</> is very special to me, a blessing. But I must say I don’t see another baby in my future.//Not in the near future anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: My <NpcName>Valentina</> is very special to me, a blessing. But I must say I don’t see another baby in my future.//Not in the near future anyway.

Text.SourceString: Changing diapers, pushing a stroller – I’ve done that life.//I don’t miss it much.
Text.LocalizedString: Changing diapers, pushing a stroller – I’ve done that life.//I don’t miss it much.

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing in the world that would stop my love for <NPCName>Suki</>.//There’ll always be a part of my heart that belongs to her.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing in the world that would stop my love for <NPCName>Suki</>.//There’ll always be a part of my heart that belongs to her.

Text.SourceString: Oh, don’t worry! I’ve moved on.//I don’t want to get back with her, but can you blame a man, <PlayerName>$Player</>? She’s the mother of my child.//<portrait=happy>Not to mention one of the most beautiful women I’ve ever laid eyes on.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, don’t worry! I’ve moved on.//I don’t want to get back with her, but can you blame a man, <PlayerName>$Player</>? She’s the mother of my child.//<portrait=happy>Not to mention one of the most beautiful women I’ve ever laid eyes on.

Text.SourceString: I keep some of the old stock in storage when it’s out of season.//Put it back out the next year. The thing about fashion is it often cycles back <Italic>fast</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep some of the old stock in storage when it’s out of season.//Put it back out the next year. The thing about fashion is it often cycles back <Italic>fast</>.

Text.SourceString: My room here in Starlet Town is smaller than I’m used to. But no complaints.//<portrait=happy>You don’t hear me complaining! Only gratitude coming from this dude.
Text.LocalizedString: My room here in Starlet Town is smaller than I’m used to. But no complaints.//<portrait=happy>You don’t hear me complaining! Only gratitude coming from this dude.

Text.SourceString: The twins are complete opposites of each other. Yeah, they might like the same food and the same weird drink, but their personalities couldn’t be more different.//<portrait=happy>My girls complete each other.
Text.LocalizedString: The twins are complete opposites of each other. Yeah, they might like the same food and the same weird drink, but their personalities couldn’t be more different.//<portrait=happy>My girls complete each other.

Text.SourceString: I‘m teaching <NpcName>Valentina</> the importance of being close to her family and visiting her uncles, even if their house is hot.//<portrait=concerned>Speaking of – Why is that, do you think? Why do they have a whole furnace inside their house, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I‘m teaching <NpcName>Valentina</> the importance of being close to her family and visiting her uncles, even if their house is hot.//<portrait=concerned>Speaking of – Why is that, do you think? Why do they have a whole furnace inside their house, huh?

Text.SourceString: It’s certainly no picnic visiting <NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</>. They should open that house a little.//Let the heat out.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s certainly no picnic visiting <NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</>. They should open that house a little.//Let the heat out.

Text.SourceString: I could never get <NpcName>Rafael</> to go out.//The man likes his solitude.
Text.LocalizedString: I could never get <NpcName>Rafael</> to go out.//The man likes his solitude.

Text.SourceString: Ah, you look dashing today. Who are you wearing?//White Flamingo?
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, you look dashing today. Who are you wearing?//White Flamingo?

Text.SourceString: Ah, that’s a nice outfit. Is it from White Flamingo?//Very suitable for the snow with that whole Winter vibe.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, that’s a nice outfit. Is it from White Flamingo?//Very suitable for the snow with that whole Winter vibe.

Text.SourceString: Stop me if you ever catch me listening to rock music, will you?//<NpcName>Pablo</> got me listening to it in his den. Couldn’t hear for two days.
Text.LocalizedString: Stop me if you ever catch me listening to rock music, will you?//<NpcName>Pablo</> got me listening to it in his den. Couldn’t hear for two days.

Text.SourceString: It’s not for me. It’s giving me bad flashbacks.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not for me. It’s giving me bad flashbacks.

Text.SourceString: To be honest, I probably knew deep down it was never going to be <NpcName>Suki</> and me.//<portrait=concerned>We… We’re different people now from who we were when we married a long time ago.
Text.LocalizedString: To be honest, I probably knew deep down it was never going to be <NpcName>Suki</> and me.//<portrait=concerned>We… We’re different people now from who we were when we married a long time ago.

Text.SourceString: Hard pill to swallow, it was. Yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: Hard pill to swallow, it was. Yeah.

Text.SourceString: I’m only here on the weekends.//Sometimes I come on Thursday, sometimes Friday. It depends on my work schedule.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m only here on the weekends.//Sometimes I come on Thursday, sometimes Friday. It depends on my work schedule.

Text.SourceString: I don’t live at the inn, no.//I have a room there when I visit my little empanada. Free of charge, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t live at the inn, no.//I have a room there when I visit my little empanada. Free of charge, of course.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been enjoying Spring so far. It’s so…springy, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been enjoying Spring so far. It’s so…springy, you know?

Text.SourceString: Ah, it’s cuddle weather. Too bad I’m single.//Hopefully, that changes soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, it’s cuddle weather. Too bad I’m single.//Hopefully, that changes soon.

Text.SourceString: My relationship status, I mean, not the weather.//<portrait=normal>I like this weather just fine. The lack of a partner, however…
Text.LocalizedString: My relationship status, I mean, not the weather.//<portrait=normal>I like this weather just fine. The lack of a partner, however…

Text.SourceString: I need to tell <NpcName>Pablo</> about the draft from my bedroom window.//It’s starting to get unbearable at night.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to tell <NpcName>Pablo</> about the draft from my bedroom window.//It’s starting to get unbearable at night.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I can fix it myself. How hard could it be?
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I can fix it myself. How hard could it be?

Text.SourceString: This is delicious. I found it in the fridge.
Text.LocalizedString: This is delicious. I found it in the fridge.

Text.SourceString: It doesn’t have anybody’s name on it.//I think it’s free to take. Want some?
Text.LocalizedString: It doesn’t have anybody’s name on it.//I think it’s free to take. Want some?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is becoming more and more like her mother as she grows up.//I couldn’t be more proud.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is becoming more and more like her mother as she grows up.//I couldn’t be more proud.

Text.SourceString: My parents used to farm a little. Well, they were blacksmiths, and they farmed on the side.//<portrait=happy>There were lots of kids. We needed some extra money.
Text.LocalizedString: My parents used to farm a little. Well, they were blacksmiths, and they farmed on the side.//<portrait=happy>There were lots of kids. We needed some extra money.

Text.SourceString: We mostly grew jackfruits and radishes. Multi-season crops. They’re cheaper to grow.
Text.LocalizedString: We mostly grew jackfruits and radishes. Multi-season crops. They’re cheaper to grow.

Text.SourceString: The twins fight all the time.//If you happen to witness one, better not get involved.
Text.LocalizedString: The twins fight all the time.//If you happen to witness one, better not get involved.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Alice</> might look timid, but that one – oof, she’s feisty too.//<portrait=normal>They’ll be okay. They always make up in the end.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Alice</> might look timid, but that one – oof, she’s feisty too.//<portrait=normal>They’ll be okay. They always make up in the end.

Text.SourceString: Having a kid is not cheap, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Ha ha!//Last night, I started thinking about how much it’ll cost for <NpcName>Valentina</> to go to university. Oof! Kept me awake for hours.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a kid is not cheap, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Ha ha!//Last night, I started thinking about how much it’ll cost for <NpcName>Valentina</> to go to university. Oof! Kept me awake for hours.

Text.SourceString: Don’t think I slept at all!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t think I slept at all!

Text.SourceString: I’ll have to set aside some time to enjoy the beach.//It’s what Summer’s for, right? It’s a pity I didn’t bring a bathing suit with me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll have to set aside some time to enjoy the beach.//It’s what Summer’s for, right? It’s a pity I didn’t bring a bathing suit with me.

Text.SourceString: Do you know if the hot spring near the forest is open for visitors again? It’d be nice to go there tonight.//<portrait=concerned>Ah, I can’t. I have a business call scheduled. Dang it!
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know if the hot spring near the forest is open for visitors again? It’d be nice to go there tonight.//<portrait=concerned>Ah, I can’t. I have a business call scheduled. Dang it!

Text.SourceString: The last time I went there, it was all dried out and dirty.//That was years ago, though.
Text.LocalizedString: The last time I went there, it was all dried out and dirty.//That was years ago, though.

Text.SourceString: I noticed people here like to dye their hair.//<portrait=happy>Saw a customer at the store the other day with bright-blue hair. What a choice!
Text.LocalizedString: I noticed people here like to dye their hair.//<portrait=happy>Saw a customer at the store the other day with bright-blue hair. What a choice!
